        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1307<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the Interim Committee</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HGL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of War</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SHL2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">21 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_War1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">War</hi>
                    </gloss> 35987. Secretary of <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_EyesOnly1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eyes Only</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_topsec1">TopSec</gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_HGL1">Harrison</persName>.</p>
                <p>All your local military advisors engaged in preparation definitely favor your pet
                        city<note n="1" xml:id="d1307fn1">The reference is to the selection of Kyoto
                        as a possible target for atomic attack. See <persName corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BHH1">Bundy</persName>,
                            <hi rend="italic">On Active Service in Peace and War</hi>, p.
                        625.</note> and would like to feel free to use it as first choice if those
                    on the ride select it out of four possible spots in the light of local
                    conditions at the time.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
